Chart Pattern Identified :  BEARISH WOLFE WAVE 

In its bearish version , the highs and lows are increasing and herald a downward reversal of an uptrend.

1) A significant maximum is formed, preferably an absolute maximum ( point 1 )
2) The price falls and forms a minimum ( point 2 )
3) The price rises and forms a subsequent maximum higher than point...
